## Problem
parseAtUri is used as a filter predicate in the needsResolution filter:
```tsx
const needsResolution = contributors.filter(
  (c) => c.needsResolution && c.identityRef && parseAtUri(c.identityRef.uri),
);
```

parseAtUri returns undefined for invalid URIs and an object for valid ones. Using it as a truthy predicate works, but it is fragile: the function is called purely for its side-effect-free return value as a boolean, not for the parsed result. The actual parsing is done again on line 66 with parseAtUri(ref.uri)!. This means parseAtUri is called twice per contributor, and the non-null assertion on line 66 is only safe because of the filter on line 60.

