## Problem
`lib/utils.ts` lines 39-41 and `lib/utils.ts` lines 79-81 hardcode `@jpeg` in CDN blob URLs:

```ts
return `https://cdn.bsky.app/img/feed_thumbnail/plain/${did}/${cid.toString()}@jpeg`;
```

This is also repeated in `convertBlobUrlToCdn` (line 80). The `@jpeg` suffix tells the Bluesky CDN to transcode the image to JPEG. For non-image blobs (e.g. GeoJSON location files, PDF evidence files) this will either fail or return corrupted data. Even for images, PNG files with transparency will lose their alpha channel.

The MIME type is available on the `BlobRef` object as `blobRef.mimeType` but is not used.

## Fix
Use the actual MIME type from the blob reference to select the correct CDN format, or use `@png` as a safer default for images. For non-image blobs, use the PDS direct URL instead of the CDN:

```ts
// Only use CDN for image blobs
if (blobRef.mimeType?.startsWith('image/')) {
  const format = blobRef.mimeType === 'image/png' ? '@png' : '@jpeg';
  return `https://cdn.bsky.app/img/feed_thumbnail/plain/${did}/${cid}${format}`;
}
// Fall back to PDS URL for non-image blobs
return `${resolvedPdsUrl}/xrpc/com.atproto.sync.getBlob?did=...`;
```

