## Problem
Fetched record values are cast directly to local Evaluation and Measurement interfaces without any runtime validation. If the server returns unexpected data (missing fields, wrong types), the cast silently succeeds and the component will render with undefined values or crash at runtime.

## Evidence
```tsx
// evaluations-section.tsx line 42
if (q.isSuccess && q.data) items.push(q.data.value as Evaluation);

// measurements-section.tsx line 51
if (q.isSuccess && q.data) items.push(q.data.value as Measurement);
```

## Fix
Add a type guard or use zod/valibot to validate the shape before casting:
```tsx
function isEvaluation(v: unknown): v is Evaluation {
  return (
    typeof v === 'object' && v !== null &&
    typeof (v as Evaluation).summary === 'string' &&
    typeof (v as Evaluation).createdAt === 'string' &&
    Array.isArray((v as Evaluation).evaluators)
  );
}

// Then:
if (q.isSuccess && q.data && isEvaluation(q.data.value)) {
  items.push(q.data.value);
}
```

Alternatively, use optional chaining in the view components to handle missing fields gracefully.

